Spicy Lentils (South Africa)

2 c. orange lentils, rinsed and picked through for twig and stone removal
1/4 c. oil
1 chopped large sweet onion
1" piece fresh ginger, grated
3 crushed garlic cloves (minced)
1 tsp coriander powder
1 tsp tumeric
1 tsp crushed cuminseed
1 tsp crushed cardamon seed
1/4 tsp cinnamon
1/2 tsp cayenne pepper
1 c. fresh tomato, diced & peeled (can use can)


Dissolve salt in enough boiling water to cover lentils. Add lentils and cook until tender, ~20min. Drain and mash with potato masher.
Heat oil in pan and fry onions and garlic until onions are golden. Add remaining ingredients and simmer for a few minutes. Stir in lentils and heat until thick.

